LEGISLATURE OF NEBRASKA
ONE HUNDRED NINTH LEGISLATURE
SECOND SESSION
LEGISLATIVE BILL 437
FINAL READING
Introduced by Riepe, 12; Hansen, 16.
Read first time January 21, 2025
Committee: Health and Human Services
1 A BILL FOR AN ACT relating to the Nebraska Health Care Certificate of
2 Need Act; to amend section 71-5848.01, Reissue Revised Statutes of
3 Nebraska; to change the validity period for a new or modified
4 certificate of need; and to repeal the original section.
5 Be it enacted by the people of the State of Nebraska,
-1-

LB437 LB437
2026 2026
1 Section 1. Section 71-5848.01, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska,
2 is amended to read:
3 71-5848.01 A new or modified certificate of need shall be valid for
4 a period of three years one year from the date of issuance and may be
5 renewed at the expiration of such period for up to one year if the holder
6 of the certificate establishes that the holder is meeting the timetable
7 or making a good faith effort to meet it. The department shall give
8 written notice to an applicant for a renewal certificate of its decision
9 within thirty days after receipt of an application. Such decision shall
10 be considered a final decision of the department for purposes of appeal.
11 If the decision is not appealed, it shall be final as of the date issued.
12 Sec. 2. Original section 71-5848.01, Reissue Revised Statutes of
13 Nebraska, is repealed.
